===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Winston Churchill|Winston Churchill]]

===Phrase===
'''[[a]] [[riddle]] [[wrap]]ped [[up]] [[in]] [[an]] [[enigma]]'''

# {{idiom}} Something very mysterious and hidden.

A form of Winston Churchill's quotation, made in a radio broadcast in October 1939:

    "I cannot forecast to you the action of Russia. It is a riddle, wrapped in a mystery, inside an enigma; but perhaps there is a key. That key is Russian national interest."

